1988 - Dragons Forever (Sammo Hung)

snippet.textDisplay: Back in 1985 - 1987, I went to a high school built on a hill, with these long, rolling corridors and each wing built above the next. In my freshman and sophomore years, my classes were all mixed up, top of the hill, bottom of the hill, etc. Every day, between classes, I would run from the top to the bottom/bottom to the top, ducking under locker doors, jumping over garbage cans, spinning around obstacles, leaping bushes, dodging hundreds of fellow students, etc. A few people thought it was fun, a couple asked me why I did it (I enjoyed it), and I even had one guy join me doing it for awhile, but most people just thought I was an asshat and called me names. Flash forward twenty years and this weird behavior has a name, and everybody thinks these dummies are heroes and they get all the credit for something some of us were doing when they were in diapers. There just is no justice in the world.
